# Toronto Rising — Linear tracking (primary responsibility)

**Linear is a primary source of truth for project state**, alongside the codebase. Agents must treat Linear synchronization as part of completing work — not an optional follow-up.

## Authoritative surfaces

| Surface | Role |
| --- | --- |
| **Linear** (`Toronto Rising` team, `TOR-*`) | Status, ownership, history, bug anchors for shipped features |
| [`.dev/RUNNING TASKLIST.md`](../../.dev/RUNNING%20TASKLIST.md) | Human/agent authoring list for planned work; every bullet has `_(TOR-XX)_` |
| [`.dev/INBOX.md`](../../.dev/INBOX.md) | Quick capture (`bug` / `intent` / `idea`); **not** authoritative for status until triaged |
| **Code + `.dev/` docs** | Implementation truth; must match Done issues |

When these diverge, **reconcile immediately** (update Linear and/or tasklist to match code reality).

## Capture vs scheduled work

- **Quick note:** one line in [`.dev/INBOX.md`](../../.dev/INBOX.md) under **Active** (prefixes optional).
- **Triage:** user says **“process the inbox”** → Phase 1: ask clarifications, park unclear items in **Needs clarification**; Phase 2: agent promotes clear items to Linear and/or RUNNING TASKLIST per [DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md § Inbox capture & triage](../../.dev/DEVELOPMENT%20WORKFLOW.md#inbox-capture--triage).

## Agent workflow (every task)

1. **Before starting** — Search Linear for related `TOR-*` issues; read matching tasklist bullet if present; skim INBOX Active if overlap is likely.
2. **When starting** — Set issue **In Progress**; confirm tasklist bullet has the correct `_(TOR-XX)_`.
3. **When finishing** — Mark **Done** (or **Canceled** if descoped) with a comment: what changed, key files, verification, commit refs. Update tasklist `[ ]` → `[x]` if applicable. Reference `TOR-XX` in commit body when committing.
4. **When discovering new work** — INBOX one-liner if capture-only; otherwise create Linear issue in the correct **domain project**, add `source:tasklist` if from tasklist, append `_(TOR-XX)_` to tasklist, set **In Progress** if starting immediately.
5. **When finding bugs on shipped features** — Create a **Bug** issue; `relatedTo` the original **Done** feature issue. Do not reopen unrelated Done issues.
6. **Inbox triage** — On “process the inbox”: Phase 1 clarify (chat + **Needs clarification**); Phase 2 promote ready items (agent chooses Backlog vs RUNNING TASKLIST).

## Domain projects

Use domain projects (not legacy Phase 1/2/3): Foundation & Tooling, Synchronization & State, Dice & Rolls, Scenes & Chronicle, Lighting & Camera, NPC & Spotlight, Soundscape & Audio, UI & HUD, Character Sheets, Players & Connection, Table Objects, Agent Reviews & Quality, Out of Scope (Workshop).

Parent epics: TOR-30 (Foundation) through TOR-43 (Workshop). Attach new issues under the matching epic via `parentId` when applicable.

## Labels

- `Feature`, `Improvement`, or `Bug`
- `source:tasklist` when the item originates from RUNNING TASKLIST
- `module:*` matching the domain (`module:dice`, `module:conditions`, etc.)

## Tools

- Linear MCP: `plugin-linear-linear` (`list_issues`, `get_issue`, `save_issue`, `save_comment`)
- Team: **Toronto Rising**
- Audit trail: [`.dev/plans/linear-alignment-log.md`](../../.dev/plans/linear-alignment-log.md)
- Full sync workflow: [`.dev/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md`](../../.dev/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md) § Linear synchronization and § Inbox capture & triage

## Non-negotiables

- **Never** leave RUNNING TASKLIST and Linear out of sync after a session.
- **Never** delete Linear issues; cancel or close with reason.
- **Never** skip creating a Done issue for shipped work — completed features are bug anchors.
- **Do not** wait for the user to ask for Linear updates; sync is part of the definition of done.
